channel.title: Project Dead Man
channel.description:
Hello MoparScape Community! Even though I am new I want to try my own server project. Not many people know me but this will create a good time to build friendship with me and the other people who shall be inside the project. I am not going to force you to do something but you may tell me what you want and I will either accept the code or decline it. I will not yell or scream at you in ways and I want to make everything the funnest it can be. I want to make this project the best it can be and the most best for players to be on. Time to explain what the project will need.
[b]Jobs Available[/b] 1. Coders 2. Webclient Maker (We need someone professional for this) 3. Advertisements (easiest I assume...) 4. Testers 5. Handler Makers 6. A Forum maker 7. Forum designer
That's all the jobs I can think of now. Now I shall explain the jobs throughout the course of this project.
[b]What do the jobs mean?[/b]
Coders Coders will make codes for the server as in voids , methods , ect. Try to reduce lag as much as possible. Try to make everything better...Minigames , Quests.
WebClient Maker We need a professional for this. Someone to make a web-client on the forums so there is no point of using a client.
Advertisements Someone to create advertisements and make sure people like them. Hopefully the people will want to join the server.
Testers The testers will test all the codes created by coders and all the Handlers created by the Handler Makers
Handler Makers These people are the ones that will take out most of the useless things in the client.java and making handlers to reduce client.java lag attacks.
Forum Maker Will make the forum for the web-client and discussion for the players.
Forum Designer The designer will make the forum look great which will make the players feel amazed how good it is.
[center]Coders - Waffles!! - blitz_9100 - Moparclient -[/center]
[center]Client Maker - HcoJustin -[/center]

If you have any questions about this please message me on MSN -- I_Heep_On_You@hotmail.com
Thanks :)
